<TITLE> Anderson to replace Kaka in Brazil friendly </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 RIO DE JANEIRO, March 23 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Manchester United's Anderson will replace the injured Kaka in the Brazil squad for Wednesday's friendly international against Sweden in London. The Brazilian Football Confederation confirmed on their Web site (http://cbfnews.uol.com.br) that World Player of the Year Kaka had been ruled out and that midfielder Anderson would step in. Brazil will also be without Ronaldinho for the game after he was left out of the squad by coach Dunga
